  "label": "Cinderwake Cableway",
  "description": "A narrow interior passage running along the ship’s braced ribs, where cable runs and iron turnbuckles remain exposed for constant inspection. Bulkheads carry soot-darkened plating and overlapping ash-seals, with rivet lines tarred against abrasive grit driven through the seams. Lanterns sit in thick glass housings behind shuttered cowls, casting slit-like light that breaks across scoured decking. Tether rings and low handholds punctuate the walls, reflecting the vessel’s design for transit under Vespera Tertius’ electrostatic gales.",
